    "card": {
      "wire": "Attaches at Position. The root (position_bias.md) declares the resting tilt a persona brings to every judgment: a scale that does not rest level, read before the evidence lands. The law makes every persona carry one.",
      "issue": "The tilt is a tree. Five motive families cut by what the lean serves -- self (the ego), coherence (the standing model), ease (the cheapest reading), belonging (the group), stake (what is already held) -- each routing through its sub-motives to the specific named bias. The root fires the motive, the family names the sub-motive, and the leaf is the bias the persona carries.",
      "require": "Two altitudes hold the engine. The law: declared once in the project's Instructions Knowledge chapter, linking the root, so a resting tilt is read for every persona. The link: each persona links, under Projection, the leaf bias it carries into the scene, which composes its family and the root with it.",
      "enforce": "Structure is checked; coherence is judged. The kit verifies the floor: the law is declared and each persona links a real leaf. Whether the tilt is true to the reading and colors the scene is semantic, taught and reviewed, never failed by the suite.",
      "setup": "Declare the law in the Instructions Knowledge chapter, linking the root. Then give the persona its bias under Projection, linking the leaf; composing it stacks the sub-motive, the family, and the root. Read it in how the persona weighs before the evidence is in."
    }
